sPAIN DAYBOOK: Treasury Auction, Bad Loans Data, House Prices

-- B y   A n g e l i n e   B e n o i t
-- 
2011-10-18T05:46:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/spain-daybook-treasury-auction-bad-loans-data-house-prices.html
Spain ’s Treasury aims to sell as
much as 5 billion euros of bills while the Public Works and
Housing Ministry publishes third-quarter  home prices .  WHAT TO WATCH:
*The Treasury aims to sell a maximum of 5 billion euros of 12-
month and 18-month bills, with results around 10.35 a.m. CET.
*Bank of Spain publishes bad loans data at around 10 a.m.  ECONOMY:
*Third-quarter home prices at 9:00 a.m. CET.
*The euro yesterday dropped against the dollar after German
Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s chief spokesman said “dreams” of an
imminent resolution to the European sovereign debt crisis aren’t
likely to be fulfilled at an Oct. 23 summit in Brussels.  EQUITIES:
*Banco Santander SA is in talks with two international funds to
sell 3 billion euros ($4.1 billion) worth of property assets,
Expansion reported, citing unidentified people with knowledge of
the talks.
*Novacaixagalicia’s bank NCG Banco yesterday said its former
joint general director Javier Garcia de Paredes agreed to
renounce most of an early retirement settlement, and that talks
to reach similar accords with other executives are ongoing.  MARKETS:
*The IBEX 35 Index fell 1.2 percent to 8,864.30.
*The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs
widened to 322 basis points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
